Sensational songstress Tems has made history at the just-concluded BET Awards 2022. She emerged winner of the ‘Best International Act’ making her the first female act to clinch the award at the ceremony, which took place at the Microsoft Theatre in Los Angeles. The “Damages” singer beat Fireboy, Dave from the UK, Dinos from France, Fally Ipupa from Congo, Little Simz from the UK, Ludmilla from Brazil, Major League Djz from South Africa, and Tayc from France; to secure the award. Receiving the historical award, Tems dedicated it to every young woman, artistes striving to live their dreams someday. She said: “BET, thank you so much for this; thank you so much. It’s an honour… I mean, this is my first award show that I’m winning something and I just want to use this as an opportunity to speak to every single young, old, whatever, every single woman watching this, every single girl watching this at home. Where I’m from, things like this don’t happen. “Where I’m from, Lagos, Nigeria; this is a dream. And as you’re watching me, I want you to imagine yourself as me because you are meant to be here too.”   G-Kross launches debut album, plans Calabar concert     I didn’t attend any church for healing- Kemi Afolabi     Wealth senseless without education – Pere   “And so, I’m dedicating this to every single young woman, every artiste, everybody that is striving and dares to dream.   “I dare you to get up from your seat and go for your dreams and fight for yourself because; you can do it. “If you’re waiting for a sign from God, take this as that sign. E go be,” she added. Before making the peace sign then walked off stage. The 27-year-old singer’s collaboration with Wizkid on his global hit, “Essence” which also featured Justin Bieber earned her a second award, “Best Collaboration.” With this feat, Tems joins the likes of Burna Boy, Wizkid and Davido who have won the prestigious BET Award for the “Best International Act” category.